properties.Name: IpAddressType
properties.Description:
The Internet Protocol (IP) has two versions currently in use (see IP version history for details). Each version has its own definition of an IP address

IPv4 uses 32-bit (4-byte) addresses, which limits the address space to 4,294,967,296 (232) possible unique addresses.  The IP version 4 address space is rapidly nearing exhaustion of available, officially assignable address blocks.

IPv6 features a larger address space than that of IPv4: addresses in IPv6 are 128 bits long versus 32 bits in IPv4.

Columns.Name: IpAddressTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an IP Address Type.

Columns.Name: IpAddressTypeName
Columns.Description: The name of an IP Address Type.

Columns.Name: IpAddressTypeDescription
Columns.Description: The description of an IP Address Type.
